@BitcoinPaymentService_HostAddress = https://localhost:7002

### Test Bitcoin Payment Service Health
GET {{BitcoinPaymentService_HostAddress}}/health

### Create Invoice (NEW APPROACH)
POST {{BitcoinPaymentService_HostAddress}}/api/bitcoin/create-invoice
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "amount": 25.00,
  "orderId": "PSP_20250918213952_D4EA99C1",
  "returnUrl": "http://localhost:3003/success",
  "buyerEmail": "colakdarie@gmail.com",
  "itemName": "Telecom Premium Package"
}

### Create QR Code Payment (OLD APPROACH)
POST {{BitcoinPaymentService_HostAddress}}/api/bitcoin/create-qr-payment
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "amount": 50.00,
  "orderId": "ORDER_123",
  "returnUrl": "https://example.com/return",
  "currency": "BTC",
  "buyerEmail": "user@example.com",
  "itemName": "Test Purchase"
}

### Get Payment Status (replace {{paymentId}} with actual payment ID)
GET {{BitcoinPaymentService_HostAddress}}/api/bitcoin/payment-status/{{paymentId}}

### Get Transaction Info (replace {{transactionId}} with actual transaction ID)
GET {{BitcoinPaymentService_HostAddress}}/api/bitcoin/transaction-info/{{transactionId}}

### CoinPayments Webhook (for testing - replace {{transactionId}} with actual transaction ID)
POST {{BitcoinPaymentService_HostAddress}}/api/bitcoin/coinpayments-webhook
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "txnId": "{{transactionId}}",
  "status": 100,
  "amount": 0.0012,
  "currency": "BTC"
}

### Weather forecast endpoint (original test endpoint)
GET {{BitcoinPaymentService_HostAddress}}/weatherforecast/
Accept: application/json
